The paper discusses the field of Artificial General Intelligence, which is primarily concerned with developing systems capable of performing any intellectual task a human being is capable of. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the process of self-organization, which is a key concept in the field of Neural Networks (cs.NE). The paper proposes a new theoretical approach to understanding intelligence, which involves the use of self-organizing networks, which is also relevant to the field of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the coordination of intelligent agents, which is relevant to the field of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the application of open-ended intelligence to robotic systems, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO).
